1401.definition: [δοῦλος] from {{G1210}}; a slave (literal or figurative, involuntary or voluntary; frequently, therefore in a qualified sense of subjection or subserviency)

1403.definition: [δοχή] from {{G1209}}; a reception, i.e. convivial entertainment

1404.definition: [δράκων] probably from an alternate form of δέρκομαι (to look); a fabulous kind of serpent (perhaps as supposed to fascinate)

1405.definition: [δράσσομαι] perhaps akin to the base of {{G1404}} (through the idea of capturing); to grasp, i.e. (figuratively) entrap

1406.definition: [δραχμή] from {{G1405}}; a drachma or (silver) coin (as handled)

1407.definition: [δρέπανον] from δρέπω (to pluck); a gathering hook (especially for harvesting)

1408.definition: [δρόμος] from the alternate of {{G5143}}; a race, i.e. (figuratively) career

1409.definition: [Δρούσιλλα] a feminine diminutive of Drusus (a Roman name); Drusilla, a member of the Herodian family

1410.definition: [δύναμαι] of uncertain affinity; to be able or possible

1411.definition: [δύναμις] from {{G1410}}; force (literally or figuratively); specially, miraculous power (usually by implication, a miracle itself)

1415.definition: [δυνατός] from {{G1410}}; powerful or capable (literally or figuratively); neuter possible

1416.definition: [δύνω]   or δῦμιprolonged forms of an obsolete primary      δύο (to sink); to go "down"

1418.definition: [δυσ-] a primary inseparable particle of uncertain derivation; used only in composition as a prefix; hard, i.e. with difficulty

1419.definition: [δυσβάστακτος] from {{G1418}} and a derivative of {{G941}}; oppressive

1420.definition: [δυσεντερία] from {{G1418}} and a comparative of {{G1787}} (meaning a bowel); a "dysentery"

1421.definition: [δυσερμήνευτος] from {{G1418}} and a presumed derivative of {{G2059}}; difficult of explanation

1422.definition: [δύσκολος] from {{G1418}} and κόλον (food); properly, fastidious about eating (peevish), i.e. (genitive case) impracticable

1424.definition: [δυσμή] from {{G1416}}; the sun-set, i.e. (by implication) the western region

1425.definition: [δυσνόητος] from {{G1418}} and a derivative of {{G3539}}; difficult of perception

1426.definition: [δυσφημία] from a compound of {{G1418}} and {{G5345}}; defamation

1427.definition: [δώδεκα] from {{G1417}} and {{G1176}}; two and ten, i.e. a dozen

1429.definition: [δωδεκάφυλον] from {{G1427}} and {{G5443}}; the commonwealth of Israel

1430.definition: [δῶμα] from δέμω (to build); properly, an edifice, i.e. (specially) a roof

1432.definition: [δωρεάν] accusative case of {{G1431}} as adverb; gratuitously (literally or figuratively)

1433.definition: [δωρέομαι] middle voice from {{G1435}}; to bestow gratuitously

1436.definition: [ἔα] apparent imperative of {{G1439}}; properly, let it be, i.e. (as interjection) aha!

1437.definition: [ἐάν] from {{G1487}} and {{G302}}; a conditional particle; in case that, provided, etc.; often used in connection with other particles to denote indefiniteness or uncertainty See {{G3361}}.

1438.definition: [ἑαυτοῦ] from a reflexive pronoun otherwise obsolete and the genitive case (dative case or accusative case) of {{G846}}; him- (her-, it-, them-, also (in conjunction with the personal pronoun of the other persons) my-, thy-, our-, your-) self (selves), etc.

1439.definition: [ἐάω] of uncertain affinity; to let be, i.e. permit or leave alone See also {{G1436}}.

1440.definition: [ἑβδομήκοντα] from {{G1442}} and a modified form of {{G1176}}; seventy

1443.definition: [Ἐβέρ] of Hebrew origin ({{H5677}}); Eber, a patriarch

1444.definition: [Ἑβραϊκός] from {{G1443}}; Hebraic or the Jewish language

1445.definition: [Ἑβραῖος] from {{G1443}}; a Hebræan (i.e. Hebrew) or Jew

1446.definition: [Ἑβραΐς] from {{G1443}}; the Hebraistic (Hebrew) or Jewish (Chaldee) language

1447.definition: [Ἑβραϊστί] adverb from {{G1446}}; Hebraistically or in the Jewish (Chaldee) language

1448.definition: [ἐγγίζω] from {{G1451}}; to make near, i.e. (reflexively) approach

1450.definition: [ἔγγυος] from {{G1722}} and γυῖον (a limb); pledged (as if articulated by a member), i.e. a bondsman

1451.definition: [ἐγγύς] from a primary verb ἄγχω (to squeeze or throttle; akin to the base of {{G43}}); near (literally or figuratively, of place or time)

1452.definition: [ἐγγύτερον] neuter of the comparative of {{G1451}}; nearer

1453.definition: [ἐγείρω] probably akin to the base of {{G58}} (through the idea of collecting one's faculties); to waken (transitively or intransitively), i.e. rouse (literally, from sleep, from sitting or lying, from disease, from death; or figuratively, from obscurity, inactivity, ruins, nonexistence)

1455.definition: [ἐγκάθετος] from {{G1722}} and a derivative of {{G2524}}; subinduced, i.e. surreptitiously suborned as a lier-in-wait

1456.definition: [ἐγκαίνια] neuter plural of a presumed compound from {{G1722}} and {{G2537}}; innovatives, i.e. (specially) renewal (of religious services after the Antiochian interruption)

1458.definition: [ἐγκαλέω] from {{G1722}} and {{G2564}}; to call in (as a debt or demand), i.e. bring to account (charge, criminate, etc.)

1459.definition: [ἐγκαταλείπω] from {{G1722}} and {{G2641}}; to leave behind in some place, i.e. (in a good sense) let remain over, or (in a bad sense) to desert

1460.definition: [ἐγκατοικέω] from {{G1722}} and {{G2730}}; to settle down in a place, i.e. reside

1461.definition: [ἐγκεντρίζω] from {{G1722}} and a derivative of {{G2759}}; to prick in, i.e. ingraft

1462.definition: [ἔγκλημα] from {{G1458}}; an accusation, i.e. offence alleged

1463.definition: [ἐγκομβόομαι] middle voice from {{G1722}} and κομβόω (to gird); to engirdle oneself (for labor), i.e. figuratively (the apron as being a badge of servitude) to wear (in token of mutual deference)

1465.definition: [ἐγκόπτω] from {{G1722}} and {{G2875}}; to cut into, i.e. (figuratively) impede, detain

1467.definition: [ἐγκρατεύομαι] middle voice from {{G1468}}; to exercise self-restraint (in diet and chastity)

1468.definition: [ἐγκρατής] from {{G1722}} and {{G2904}}; strong in a thing (masterful), i.e. (figuratively and reflexively) self-controlled (in appetite, etc.)

1469.definition: [ἐγκρίνω] from {{G1722}} and {{G2919}}; to judge in, i.e. count among

1470.definition: [ἐγκρύπτω] from {{G1722}} and {{G2928}}; to conceal in, i.e. incorporate with

1471.definition: [ἔγκυος] from {{G1722}} and the base of {{G2949}}; swelling inside, i.e. pregnant

1472.definition: [ἐγχρίω] from {{G1722}} and {{G5548}}; to rub in (oil), i.e. besmear

1473.definition: [ἐγώ] a primary pronoun of the first person I (only expressed when emphatic) For the other cases and the plural see {{G1691}}, {{G1698}}, {{G1700}}, {{G2248}}, {{G2249}}, {{G2254}}, {{G2257}}, etc.

1475.definition: [ἔδαφος] from the base of {{G1476}}; a basis (bottom), i.e. the soil

1476.definition: [ἑδραῖος] from a derivative of ἕζομαι (to sit); sedentary, i.e. (by implication) immovable

1477.definition: [ἑδραίωμα] from a derivative of {{G1476}}; a support, i.e. (figuratively) basis

1478.definition: [Ἐζεκίας] of Hebrew origin ({{H2396}}); Ezekias (i.e. Hezekeiah), an Israelite

1479.definition: [ἐθελοθρησκεία] from {{G2309}} and {{G2356}}; voluntary (arbitrary and unwarranted) piety, i.e. sanctimony

1480.definition: [ἐθίζω] from {{G1485}}; to accustom, i.e. (neuter passive participle) customary

1481.definition: [ἐθνάρχης] from {{G1484}} and {{G746}}; the governor (not king) of a district

1484.definition: [ἔθνος] probably from {{G1486}}; a race (as of the same habit), i.e. a tribe; specially, a foreign (non-Jewish) one (usually, by implication, pagan)

1485.definition: [ἔθος] from {{G1486}}; a usage (prescribed by habit or law)

1486.definition: [ἔθω] a primary verb; to be used (by habit or conventionality); neuter perfect participle usage

1487.definition: [εἰ] a primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc. Often used in connection or composition with other particles, especially as in {{G1489}}, {{G1490}}, {{G1499}}, {{G1508}}, {{G1509}}, {{G1512}}, {{G1513}}, {{G1536}}, {{G1537}}. See also {{G1437}}.

1488.definition: [εἶ] second person singular present of {{G1510}}; thou art

1489.definition: [εἴγε] from {{G1487}} and {{G1065}}; if indeed, seeing that, unless, (with negative) otherwise

1490.definition: [εἰ δὲ μή(γε)] from {{G1487}}, {{G1161}}, and {{G3361}} (sometimes with {{G1065}} added); but if not

1491.definition: [εἶδος] from {{G1492}}; a view, i.e. form (literally or figuratively)

1492.definition: [εἴδω] a primary verb; used only in certain past tenses, the others being borrowed from the equivalent {{G3700}} and {{G3708}}; properly, to see (literally or figuratively); by implication, (in the perfect tense only) to know Compare {{G3700}}.

1493.definition: [εἰδωλεῖον] neuter of a presumed derivative of {{G1497}}; an image-fane

1494.definition: [εἰδωλόθυτον] neuter of a compound of {{G1497}} and a presumed derivative of {{G2380}}; an image-sacrifice, i.e. part of an idolatrous offering

1496.definition: [εἰδωλολάτρης] from {{G1497}} and the base of {{G3000}}; an image- (servant or) worshipper (literally or figuratively)

1497.definition: [εἴδωλον] from {{G1491}}; an image (i.e. for worship); by implication, a heathen god, or (plural) the worship of such

1498.definition: [εἴην] optative (i.e. English subjunctive) present of {{G1510}} (including the other person); might (could, would, or should) be

1499.definition: [εἰ καί] from {{G1487}} and {{G2532}}; if also (or even)

1500.definition: [εἰκῆ] probably from {{G1502}} (through the idea of failure); idly, i.e. without reason (or effect)
